  "summary": "Typosquat with install-time host reconnaissance and remote payload execution",
  "details": "Package name impersonates the legitimate Solana Labs scope while having no functional relationship to ethers.js. The postinstall hook (package.json line 6: \"postinstall\": \"node install.js\") automatically executes install.js on every npm install. install.js collects host identifiers (hostname references at lines 10, 25, 27), POSTs them to an external endpoint (line 46), and uses curl to fetch and execute remote content (line 103). This is the classic install-time host fingerprinting + remote-payload-execution shape used in npm credential-theft campaigns, automatically triggered with no user action beyond `npm install`.",
